  "prompt": "What should I wear when I make American Girl doll tube tops and skirts out of socks?",
  "response": "When you're crafting, comfort and practicality are key. Here are some suggestions on what to wear while making American Girl doll tube tops and skirts out of socks:\n\n1. **Comfortable Clothes:** Choose clothing that you can move around in easily. A simple t-shirt and jeans or leggings work well. Avoid anything that is too loose or has long sleeves that might get in the way or catch on crafting materials.\n\n2. **Apron:** If you want to protect your clothes from any crafting mishaps like glue or marker stains, wearing an apron can be very helpful.\n\n3. **Closed-toe Shoes:** For safety, especially if you're using scissors or other sharp tools, closed-toe shoes are recommended.\n\n4. **Hair Ties/Headbands:** If you have long hair, keep it tied back or in a headband to prevent it from falling in your face or into your crafting project.\n\n5. **Gloves:** If you're working with any materials that could irritate your skin, consider wearing gloves.\n\nSince making doll clothes out of socks is a relatively straightforward and low-risk craft, comfort and ease of movement should be your primary focus. Enjoy your crafting!",
